indexData.dwc:locationRemarks: Pecos River Drainage. Dry cave.  Fossils from fill surrounding the sink known as Lost Valley and, with merging of utep 17, Lost Valley itself.  Originally limited to the upper level, including the funnel portion of the sink.  A large fissure in the ceiling clogged with boulders is the obvious source.  Fossils in the upper level occur from the surface to at least 20 cm and probably much deeper.

indexData.dwc:locationRemarks: Pecos River Drainage. Dry cave.  Fossils from fill surrounding the sink known as Lost Valley and, with merging of utep 17, Lost Valley itself.  Originally limited to the upper level, including the funnel portion of the sink.  A large fissure in the ceiling clogged with boulders is the obvious source.  Fossils in the upper level occur from the surface to at least 20 cm and probably much deeper.

data.dwc:locationRemarks: Pecos River Drainage. Dry cave.  Fossils from fill surrounding the sink known as Lost Valley and, with merging of utep 17, Lost Valley itself.  Originally limited to the upper level, including the funnel portion of the sink.  A large fissure in the ceiling clogged with boulders is the obvious source.  Fossils in the upper level occur from the surface to at least 20 cm and probably much deeper.
